*How to run the CHATBOT*

1) We have used tensorflow in the backend so you will have to run it in python 3.6 environment (since tensorflow is not availible in python 3.7 yet).
2) Install keras, nltk, json, pickle and tensorflow in the 3.6 environment.
3) Now run the file named 'chatgui.py' and the chatbot will be on your screen and u can start interacting with it.

*DISCLAIMER*

After following all of the above steps it might occue that it throws an error or prompt a message saying something is missing and the steps to download it. 
All those errors and prompts can be solved by some steps depending on what error it shows, so we kindly request you to take care of it.